itemDescription: British politician (1783-1843), Member of Parliament for County Wexford, Ireland in 1834

wikipedia_page.main: Cadwallader Waddy (15 February 1783 – 7 February 1843) was an Anglo-Irish soldier and politician who sat for six months as Member of the UK Parliament for County Wexford, Ireland, in 1834.

response: He married Elizabeth Waddy, daughter of Richard Waddy  of Clougheast Castle, County Wexford, a member of a prominent local  family,  who were descended from  Cromwellian  settlers, and his wife Penelope Hatchell, daughter of Nicholas Hatchell.
